perl-net-dns|-----handy-ruler------------------------------------------------------|
perl-net-dns: perl-net-dns (DNS resolver modules for Perl)
perl-net-dns:
perl-net-dns: Net::DNS is a collection of Perl modules that act as a Domain Name
perl-net-dns: System (DNS) resolver. It allows the programmer to perform DNS queries
perl-net-dns: that are beyond the capabilities of gethostbyname and gethostbyaddr.
perl-net-dns: The programmer should be somewhat familiar with the format of a DNS
perl-net-dns: packet and its various sections. See RFC 1035 or DNS and BIND (Albitz
perl-net-dns: & Liu) for details.
perl-net-dns:
perl-net-dns: http://www.net-dns.org/
perl-net-dns: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
